                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>A former owner's note in an early modern hand on <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/> states (in Latin) that <quote>most beloved father <gap quantity="7" unit="chars" reason="damage"/> gave me this book</quote>, with the name of the donor having been erased.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>On <locus from="123r" to="123r" scheme="folios"/>, an early modern hand has written in Swedish: <quote>Come Holy Spirit Lord God visit our hearts and bestow good spirits upon His Majesty's dutiful servant</quote> and a monogram, possibly <quote>RO</quote>.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>Previously no. 10 in the collection of <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/100536">Nils Reinhold Brocman</persName>, book collector and librarian at the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100004">Royal Library</orgName> and <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100059">Antiquities Archive</orgName>. Upon his death in <date when="1770"/>, a large part of his book collection was donated to the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100059">Antiquities Archive</orgName>.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition>
                            <p>Transferred to the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100004">National Library</orgName> from the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100059">Antiquities Archive</orgName>.</p>
                        </acquisition>
