                                <p>
                                    <locus from="1r" to="90r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>In the margins, psalm numbers in ink in an early modern or near contemporary hand. Psalm 39 erroneously numbered as <quote>29</quote> (<locus from="30r" to="30r" scheme="folios"/>). Psalm 108 erroneously numbered as <quote>107</quote> (<locus from="81v" to="81v" scheme="folios"/>), and from here until Psalm 118 (<locus from="86v" to="86v" scheme="folios"/>) the numbering is behind by one, with corrections in pencil by a modern hand below. Psalm 118:17 is numbered as <quote>118</quote> (<locus from="87r" to="87r" scheme="folios"/>), 118:33 as <quote>119</quote> (<locus from="87v" to="87v" scheme="folios"/>), 118:49 as <quote>120</quote> (<locus from="88v" to="88v" scheme="folios"/>), 118:65 as <quote>121</quote> (<locus from="89r" to="89r" scheme="folios"/>), 118:81 as <quote>122</quote> (<locus from="89v" to="89v" scheme="folios"/>), 118:97 as <quote>123</quote> (<locus from="90r" to="90r" scheme="folios"/>), with the modern correcting hand
                                        adding <quote>118</quote> from <locus from="88v" to="88v" scheme="folios"/> ff. After this, the numbering in ink disappears, but the modern numbering in pencil - now in square brackets - continues from Psalm 119 (<locus from="93r" to="93r" scheme="folios"/>) until the end.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="123r" to="123r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Covering the top half of the page, in black ink by an early modern hand: <quote>Kom Helige Ande Herre God besök wåra hiertan och gif Kongl.<hi rend="super">a</hi> Mai.<hi rend="super">tts</hi> tropliktig tienare godt mod</quote>; below, in the same ink and style, a large monogram: <quote>RO</quote>(?). Bottom right corner, in ink: a word, faded and difficult to make out.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="123v" to="123v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Pen trials in the same hand and style as the recto: <quote>Denna</quote> and two flourished <quote>R</quote>s (or <quote>K</quote>s?).</note>
                                </p>
                            </additions>
                            <decoDesc>
                                <p>Main text in brown ink. Larger decorated initials at Ps. 1, 26, 38, 52, 68, 80, 97, 109, corresponding to the secular cursus (Sunday-Monday matins, and Sunday vespers).</p>
                                <decoNote type="initials">
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>: illuminated historiated opening initial <quote>B</quote> over 9 lines in mauve and blue shades alternating in 4 sections, with baubles in the darker shade. Background in gold leaf. In the counter space, king David, crowned and dressed in a blue mantle lined with ermine, seated on a green throne, playing the harp, and surrounded by four attendants dressed in orange and green, one of whom is holding a sword. A pattern of tiles in black and yellow creates a sense of depth in the space. The marginal border consists of thin straight double stalks, where one part is in gold leaf and the other alternates between mauve and blue sections. Soft swirling intertwining acanthus leaves in mainly red/mauve and blue decorate the edges and corners of the stalks. Green and orange occur occasionally. The straight sections between the acanthus leaves are adorned by sheer peacock-imitating feathers with tiny dots in green
                                        or gold leaf at the ends. The border fills much of the marginal space, partly due to the secondary trimming of the book pages. All decorations are outlined in black and the coloured areas are highlighted in white. <locus from="18v" to="18v" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="29r" to="29r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="39r" to="39r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="49r" to="49r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="61r" to="61r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="72v" to="72v" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="82v" to="82v" scheme="folios"/>: psalm initials over 6-9 lines; letter bodies alternating in 2-4 sections of mauve and blue shades with baubles in the darker shade (<locus from="29r" to="29r" scheme="folios"/> in all blue). Quadrangular background in gold leaf with small hollowed out roundels at the corners. In the counter space, swirling acanthus leaves mainly in blues and mauves, but also some greens, reds, and yellows. Marginal borders of acanthus
                                        leaves, peacock feathers, and small flowers in the same colour scheme extending into and filling the left, upper, and lower margin. All decorations are outlined in black and the colours are highlighted in white. <locus from="1v" to="116v" scheme="folios"/>: plain psalm or section initials over 2 lines in blue with flourishing in red extending into the left margin. <locus from="1v" to="116v" scheme="folios"/> plain initials over 1 line alternating in red and blue, and on <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>, in blue and gold leaf. <locus from="117r" to="122v" scheme="folios"/>: plain capital <quote>KL</quote> in blue with simple quadrangular pen-flourishing in red at the head of each month.</p>
                                    <p> For further description of the decoration, see <ref target="http://urn.kb.se/resolve?urn=urn:nbn:se:alvin:portal:record-472901">Eva Lindqvist Sandgren</ref>.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                            </decoDesc>
